title: Easy Chicken Stew
directions: Slow Cooker Method: Place cauliflower, corn, carrot, celery, garlic and onion in slow cooker. Stir in salsa, place chicken on top and add broth. Cook on HIGH for 3-4 hours, or LOW for 4-5 hours. Shred chicken with 2 forks, place in bowls and garnish with fresh chopped parsley.
ingredients: 4 x 4 oz chicken breasts, chopped into chunks (stove top method) , left whole (slow cooker method) *could also use rotisserie chicken breasts
1/2 medium cauliflower, chopped into smaller florets
1 cup jarred salsa (mild or hot, whatever your preference)
